  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "A support desk answers dozens of these a day. The reader on the other end wants two things: to be heard, and to be helped."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "Warmth and speed are not at odds. A reply that lands fast and reads kindly is the whole craft here."
    },
    {
      "type": "exercise",
      "target": "Hi Mark, thank you for reaching out, and I'm sorry to hear about the trouble with order #8432. I've checked the shipment, and it appears the parcel was delayed at",
      "finger": "purple",
      "hint": "Empathetic email at speed"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "A phrase like \"thank you for reaching out\" should arrive without thought, so your attention stays on the customer's actual problem."
    },
